crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_raw: alert udp $EXTERNAL_NET 53 -> $HOME_NET any ( msg:"MALWARE-CNC DNS Fast Flux attempt"; flow:to_client; content:"|00 01|",depth 2,offset 4; byte_test:2,>,1,0,relative; byte_test:1,=,1,2,bitmask 0x80; content:"|00 01 00 01|",distance 6; content:"|00 01 00 01 00 00 00 05|",distance 0; metadata:policy max-detect-ips drop; service:dns; reference:url,attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1568/001/; classtype:trojan-activity; sid:57756; rev:2; )

crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_msg: POLICY-OTHER HTTP request by IPv4 address attempt
crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_raw: alert tcp any any -> any $HTTP_PORTS ( msg:"POLICY-OTHER HTTP request by IPv4 address attempt"; flow:to_server,established; http_header; content:"Host:",fast_pattern,nocase; pcre:"/^Host\x3a\s*(?:(?:25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|[01]?[0-9]?[0-9])\.){3}(?:25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|[01]?[0-9]?[0-9])\s*:?\s*\d*\s*$/smi"; service:http; reference:url,www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec15.html; classtype:policy-violation; sid:50447; rev:1; )

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects unusual processes accessing desktop.ini, which can be leveraged to alter how Explorer displays a folder's content (i.e. renaming files) without changing them on disk.

Detects modification of the registry settings used for Internet Explorer and other Windows components that use these settings. An attacker can abuse this registry key to add a domain to the trusted sites Zone or insert JavaScript for persistence
